text: Anne Frank is a single released by Swedish noise rock band Brainbombs in 1990 by Big Brothel Records. With the songs, the record also features a blank B-side. Anne Frank's lyrical content is very dark. As it talks about killing, raping and mutilating her. The song is also sung by Jonas rather than Peter, because "he [Peter] was so badly hung over he couldn't make it." == Track listing == == References == Category:1990 albums Category:Rock albums''' Category:Brainbombs songs
